<LegalLayout title="Privacy Policy" lastUpdated="May 3, 2026">

<h2>1. Introduction</h2>
<p>
  LasagnaFi, Inc. ("we," "us," or "our") operates the LasagnaFi personal finance platform.
  This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, store, and protect your information when
  you use our Service. We are committed to keeping your financial data private and secure.
</p>

<h2>2. Information We Collect</h2>

<h3>Account Information</h3>
<p>When you create an account, we collect:</p>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Email address</strong> — used for authentication and account recovery</li>
  <li><strong>Password</strong> — stored as a bcrypt hash; we never store or see your plaintext password</li>
</ul>

<h3>Financial Profile</h3>
<p>You may optionally provide financial profile details to enable personalized features:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Date of birth, annual income, filing status, state of residence</li>
  <li>Employment type, risk tolerance, target retirement age</li>
  <li>Employer 401(k) match percentage, HSA/HDHP eligibility</li>
  <li>Dependent count, PSLF eligibility</li>
</ul>

<h3>Bank and Financial Data (via Plaid)</h3>
<p>If you choose to connect your bank accounts, we receive the following from Plaid:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Account names, types, subtypes, and masked account numbers</li>
  <li>Account balances and available funds</li>
  <li>Transaction history (date, merchant, amount, category)</li>
  <li>Investment holdings and securities (tickers, quantities, prices, cost basis)</li>
</ul>
<p>
  We store encrypted Plaid access tokens using AES-256-GCM encryption. Plaid access tokens are
  never stored in plaintext. We sync your bank data periodically (every 4 hours) while your
  connection is active.
</p>

<h3>AI Conversations</h3>
<p>
  When you use the AI chat feature, we store your conversation history (messages, tool calls,
  and responses) in your database. This data is used to maintain your chat threads and provide context.
</p>

<h3>Tax Documents</h3>
<p>
  If you upload tax documents, they are stored in your database. Extracted data is used for
  tax optimization analysis.
</p>

<h3>Session Data</h3>
<p>
  We use a single session cookie (<code>lasagna_session</code>) for authentication. This cookie:
</p>
<ul>
  <li>Contains a JWT token signed with HMAC-SHA256</li>
  <li>Is httpOnly, secure, and sameSite</li>
  <li>Expires after 7 days</li>
  <li>Is used solely for authentication — not tracking</li>
</ul>

<h2>3. How We Use Your Information</h2>
<p>We use your information to:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Authenticate you and maintain your session</li>
  <li>Display your financial dashboard, net worth, and spending analysis</li>
  <li>Run retirement simulations (Monte Carlo, backtesting) using your financial data</li>
  <li>Provide debt payoff strategies and tax optimization insights</li>
  <li>Analyze your investment portfolio against 175+ tracked securities</li>
  <li>Power AI chat responses about your financial situation</li>
  <li>Generate financial goals and action items</li>
</ul>

<h2>4. AI Data Anonymization</h2>
<p>
  <strong>Your personal identity is never sent to AI providers.</strong> Before any data reaches
  an AI model, we apply an anonymization layer that:
</p>
<ul>
  <li>Strips your name, email, and all personally identifiable information</li>
  <li>Replaces bank and institution names with generic tokens</li>
  <li>Removes account numbers and routing numbers</li>
  <li>Sends only numerical data: balances, allocations, spending patterns, and percentages</li>
</ul>
<p>
  AI providers (accessed through OpenRouter) see financial patterns, not your identity. Your
  conversation history is stored in your database, not retained by AI providers beyond their
  standard processing window.
</p>

<h2>5. Data Sharing</h2>
<p>We do not sell, rent, or trade your personal information. We share data only with:</p>
<ul>
  <li>
    <strong>Plaid Inc.</strong> — to access your bank account data. Plaid acts as an intermediary
    between you and your financial institutions. See
    <a href="https://plaid.com/legal/#end-user-privacy-policy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Plaid's Privacy Policy</a>.
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>AI model providers (via OpenRouter)</strong> — anonymized financial data only, as
    described in Section 4. See
    <a href="https://openrouter.ai/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">OpenRouter's Privacy Policy</a>.
  </li>
</ul>
<p>
  We do not use analytics services, advertising networks, or tracking pixels. We do not share
  your data with any other third parties.
</p>
<p>
  <strong>Third-party data practices.</strong> Once data is shared with Plaid or AI model providers
  in accordance with this policy, it is subject to their respective privacy policies and practices.
  We are not responsible for and have no control over the privacy practices, data handling, or
  security measures of any third-party service. We encourage you to review the privacy policies
  of these third parties.
</p>

<h2>6. Data Storage and Security</h2>
<p>Your data is protected by:</p>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Encryption at rest</strong> — Plaid access tokens are encrypted with AES-256-GCM</li>
  <li><strong>Secure password storage</strong> — passwords are hashed with bcrypt</li>
  <li><strong>Signed session tokens</strong> — JWTs signed with HMAC-SHA256</li>
  <li><strong>Secure cookies</strong> — httpOnly, secure, sameSite attributes</li>
  <li><strong>Infrastructure</strong> — hosted on Google Cloud Platform with standard security controls</li>
</ul>
<p>
  While we implement industry-standard security measures, <strong>no method of electronic storage or
  transmission over the Internet is 100% secure.</strong> We cannot guarantee absolute security of
  your data. We are not liable for any unauthorized access, data breaches, or data loss caused by
  factors beyond our reasonable control, including but not limited to attacks on third-party
  infrastructure, compromised user credentials, or vulnerabilities in third-party services.
</p>

<h2>7. Data Retention</h2>
<p>
  We retain your data for as long as your account is active. Financial data (balances, transactions,
  holdings) is retained to provide historical analysis and trend tracking.
</p>
<p>
  When you delete your account, we delete all associated data including your financial profile,
  connected accounts, transaction history, chat conversations, and uploaded documents.
</p>

<h2>8. Your Rights</h2>
<p>You have the right to:</p>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Access</strong> your data — your dashboard displays all data we have about you</li>
  <li><strong>Delete</strong> your account and all associated data</li>
  <li><strong>Disconnect</strong> bank accounts at any time, which revokes Plaid access tokens</li>
  <li><strong>Export</strong> your data from the Service</li>
  <li><strong>Self-host</strong> — run LasagnaFi on your own infrastructure for complete data sovereignty</li>
</ul>

<h3>California Residents (CCPA)</h3>
<p>
  If you are a California resident, you have additional rights under the California Consumer
  Privacy Act, including the right to know what personal information we collect, the right to
  delete it, and the right to opt out of the sale of personal information. We do not sell
  personal information.
</p>

<h3>European Residents (GDPR)</h3>
<p>
  If you are in the European Economic Area, you have rights under the General Data Protection
  Regulation including access, rectification, erasure, restriction of processing, data portability,
  and the right to object. Our legal basis for processing is your consent (which you can withdraw
  at any time) and legitimate interest in providing the Service.
</p>

<h2>9. Cookies</h2>
<p>
  We use exactly one cookie: <code>lasagna_session</code>. It is a functional authentication
  cookie required for the Service to work. We do not use analytics cookies, advertising cookies,
  or any third-party tracking cookies.
</p>

<h2>10. Children's Privacy</h2>
<p>
  The Service is not intended for users under 18 years of age. We do not knowingly collect
  information from children. If you believe a child has provided us with personal information,
  please contact us and we will delete it.
</p>

<h2>11. Data Accuracy</h2>
<p>
  Financial data displayed in the Service is sourced from third parties (including Plaid and your
  financial institutions) and may be delayed, inaccurate, or incomplete. We do not independently
  verify the accuracy of data received from third-party providers. You are responsible for
  verifying the accuracy of your financial data. We are not liable for any errors in data
  provided by third-party services.
</p>

<h2>12. Changes to This Policy</h2>
<p>
  We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of material changes
  by posting the updated policy with a revised "last updated" date. Your continued use of the
  Service constitutes acceptance of the updated policy.
</p>

<h2>13. Contact</h2>
<p>
  If you have questions about this Privacy Policy or your data, contact us at
  <a href="mailto:privacy@lasagnafi.com">privacy@lasagnafi.com</a>.
</p>

</LegalLayout>
